0m breaststroke, and settled for joint silver.\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 633, \"end\": 643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kimberley Woods also took bronze in the women's individual kayak.\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kimberley Woods\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\"}, {\"begin\": 853, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"score\": 0.9981035439962849, \"rank\": 0.0019000593749000075, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more on Monday's Paris successes, The Standard podcast is joined by reporter Robert Dex, who's been covering developments.\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998765361, \"rank\": 1.235316723676334e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evening_Standard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.675194035896894e-30, \"text\": \"The Standard\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evening_Standard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evening_Standard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In part two, in her first major speech as chancellor, Rachel Reeves identifies a \\u00a320 billion black hole in government spending as she seeks to pin the blame for future tax rises on Tory profligacy.\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1043, \"end\": 1056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Reeves\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachel Reeves\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Reeves\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Reeves\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"score\": 0.9997197790607679, \"rank\": 0.0002800903280567418, \"text\": \"Tory\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reeves's spending cut targets include more empty public buildings sell-offs, plus slashing government investment on some road-building projects - and there is concerns about the future of central London's High Speed 2 rail link.\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1384, \"end\": 1390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997578125042, \"rank\": 2.419810772301784e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have policy analysis, plus the latest on the Conservative leadership race, with Evening Standard political editor, Nicholas Cecil.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1536, \"end\": 1544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.9873341404854046, \"rank\": 0.01270649702558388, \"text\": \"Nicholas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nichola